    <p>Most beehives have two deeps.  The deeps are where the queen lays eggs and the worker bees take care of the brood. The bees will also store honey and pollen in the deeps. &quot;Brood&quot; refers to the stages of the larvae development after the queen lays her eggs in the brood cells.</p>

